Build a fullscreen cinematic 3D scroll website, visually similar to the reference image: a dark futuristic indoor exhibition corridor with glowing image screens.

This is a 3D experience, not a normal flat website.

Core concept:
A long, dark museum-like corridor. The user scrolls and the camera moves forward slowly through the corridor. Along the way, 5-6 photo panels appear like illuminated digital exhibition boards. The feeling should be immersive, cinematic, mysterious, premium, and emotional.

Tech stack:
- Next.js
- React Three Fiber
- Drei
- Three.js
- GSAP ScrollTrigger
- Lenis smooth scroll
- Tailwind CSS

Scene layout:
- Fullscreen fixed 3D canvas
- Long rectangular corridor extending deep on the Z axis
- Dark glossy reflective floor
- Tall dark walls on left and right
- Ceiling with repeated warm rectangular lights
- Thin golden light strips running along the ceiling and wall edges
- Repeated vertical columns on both sides
- Strong depth perspective
- Background fades into darkness with fog

Camera behavior:
- Camera starts at the corridor entrance
- As the user scrolls, camera moves forward along the Z axis
- Page height around 500vh
- Canvas stays fixed while scroll controls camera movement
- Use GSAP ScrollTrigger with scrub:true
- Add subtle camera sway on X/Y for cinematic movement
- Do not rotate camera too much; keep it looking forward into the corridor

Photo panels:
- Use 5-6 test images first
- Place photo panels at different depths along the corridor
- Some panels on the left, some on the right, some near the center
- Each panel should be a vertical or square digital screen
- Panels should have thick dark frame
- Panels should emit soft colored glow
- Panels should slightly reflect on the glossy floor
- Panels should face the camera
- When the camera gets close to a panel, it becomes brighter and scales slightly
- When far away, it should be darker and softer

Interaction:
- User can click a photo panel
- Open fullscreen dark modal
- Show large image, title, caption, and close button
- Modal should feel premium and minimal

